						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the Kuraṅganātha temple.</p>						

						<p>On palaeographical grounds this may be assigned to the 10-11th century.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a grant of land, purchased for 55 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju.</hi> It mentions Nakkaṉārāyaṇi-Tiruvi•••• the wife of Ōmachcha[Nārā]ṇa Kiṇaṉ and Tiyambakaṉ Māṉaṉ, the <hi rend="italic">madhyasthan</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">paraḍai.</hi> Mahēndra[maṅgalam], a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> mentioned in this record is obviously an ancient name of Śrīnivāsanallūr.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
